: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kunth) Britton." box="[406,852,151,176]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hypochaeris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="chillensis">
<emphasis box="[406,663,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Hypochaeris chillensis</emphasis>
(Kunth) Britton.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,464]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,188,213]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Leaf mine.</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[345,482,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 26–32" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1820,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,193,1800]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1437,193,1800]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 26–32. leaf mines; 26: Agromyza arundinariae spec. nov. on Arundinaria tecta; 27: same; 28: A. indistincta spec. nov. on Dichanthelium; 29: Ophiomyia beckeri (Hendel) on Sonchus; 30: Ophiomyia sp. 1 on Hypochaeris chillensis, lower leaf surface; 31: same, upper leaf surface; 32: Ophiomyia sp. 2 on Pyrrhopappus carolinianus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2612621/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Figs. 30–31</figureCitation>
) The single photographed mine was whitish, beginning as a narrow, linear track on the lower leaf surface, then entering the midrib and petiole, where most feeding took place, including on the upper leaf surface, where there was a blotch-like expansion into the blade.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,612,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,464]" box="[199,612,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Puparium.</emphasis>
